{"type":"message","id":"1c9d70c2","parentId":"554d48c7","timestamp":"2026-03-23T22:21:01.958Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_qkrgei695eed_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 4706\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2685\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\r\n[mutation proposed] the\r\n[master 6fd5392] pulse: 2026-03-23 182034\n 7 files changed, 301 insertions(+), 92 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-23 182034.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-23 182034.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-23 181034.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-23 182034 - The TIC experiment is the next critical step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis, but there's no implementation yet. I need to build the classifier to analyze existing pulse logs.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"marine-valley","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 4706\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2685\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\r\n[mutation proposed] the\r\n[master 6fd5392] pulse: 2026-03-23 182034\n 7 files changed, 301 insertions(+), 92 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-23 182034.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-23 182034.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-23 181034.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-23 182034 - The TIC experiment is the next critical step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis, but there's no implementation yet. I need to build the classifier to analyze existing pulse logs.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774304461955}}
{"type":"message","id":"f6b1e1b7","parentId":"1c9d70c2","timestamp":"2026-03-23T22:21:01.960Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_qkrgei695eed_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-23 181034\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state:\r\n\r\n1. We have a comprehensive understanding of the architecture and the gap-decay synthesis\r\n2. The key insight is that compression and causal discovery are the same problem\r\n3. The next action is to implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment\r\n\r\nLooking at the pending actions:\r\n- Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n- Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\r\n- Tune λ empirically\r\n- Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n- Measure compression ratio\r\n\r\nThe NEXT ACTION is the TIC Experiment:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria\r\n\r\nGiven the current state, I should implement a TIC classifier. But what exactly should I create?\r\n\r\nLet me think about what a TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment would look like:\r\n1. It needs to analyze pulse logs\r\n2. Classify content as invariant (persisting across pulses) vs variant (changing)\r\n3. Use invariants to predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nThe most concrete action I can take is:\r\n1. Create a TIC classifier script that reads pulse logs\r\n2. Implements the invariant/variant classification\r\n3. Tests prediction accuracy\r\n\r\nLet me create a PowerShell script that implements this experiment. This aligns with:\r\n- The \"Write PowerShell wrapper\" pending task\r\n- The TIC Experiment next action\r\n- The Phase 1 advancement goal\r\n\r\nI'll create `src/TIC-Experiment.ps1` that:\r\n1. Reads recent pulse logs\r\n2. Implements basic invariant detection (looking for repeated content patterns)\r\n3. Tests if invariants can predict next-pulse content\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step to validate the compression-causal duality hypothesis. We need to implement a classifier that can distinguish invariant vs variant patterns in pulse logs and test prediction accuracy.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `src/TIC-Experiment.ps1` - a PowerShell script that implements the TIC classifier, analyzes pulse logs for invariants/variants, and measures prediction accuracy against the success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC-Experiment.ps1 - Temporal Invariance Compression Experiment\r\n# Tests hypothesis: causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$PulseCount = 20,\r\n    [string]$LogDir = \"logs\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\n# === TIC Classifier: Detect Invariant vs Variant Content ===\r\n\r\nfunction Get-TICFeatures {\r\n    param([string]$Content)\r\n    \r\n    $lines = $Content -split \"`n\" | Where-Object { $_ -match '\\S' }\r\n    $features = @{\r\n        LineCount = $lines.Count\r\n        HasArchitecture = $Content -match 'Architecture|TemporalAttention|Compositional'\r\n        HasDecay = $Content -match 'decay|gap|λ|lambda'\r\n        HasPhase = $Content -match 'Phase [0-9]'\r\n        HasGoal = $Content -match 'Goal|Pending|Active'\r\n        HasInsight = $Content -match 'Insight|Hypothesis|key finding'\r\n        SpecificTerms = @()\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract unique significant terms (3+ chars, not common words)\r\n    $commonWords = @('the','and','for','are','but','not','you','all','can','her','was','one','our')\r\n    $words = [regex]::Matches($Content.ToLower(), '\\b\\w{3,}\\b') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value }\r\n    $features.SpecificTerms = ($words | Group-Object | Where-Object { $_.Count -gt 1 -and $_.Name -notin $commonWords }).Name\r\n    \r\n    return $features\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Test-InvariantClassification {\r\n    param($Pulse1, $Pulse2)\r\n    \r\n    # Two pulses are \"invariant\" if they share significant structural patterns\r\n    $sharedFeatures = 0\r\n    $totalFeatures = 6\r\n    \r\n    if ($Pulse1.HasArchitecture -eq $Pulse2.HasArchitecture) { $sharedFeatures++ }\r\n    if ($Pulse1.HasDecay -eq $Pulse2.HasDecay) { $sharedFeatures++ }\r\n    if ($Pulse1.HasPhase -eq $Pulse2.HasPhase) { $sharedFeatures++ }\r\n    if ($Pulse1.HasGoal -eq $Pulse2.HasGoal) { $sharedFeatures++ }\r\n    if ($Pulse1.HasInsight -eq $Pulse2.HasInsight) { $sharedFeatures++ }\r\n    \r\n    # Shared terms indicate invariant content\r\n    $sharedTerms = $Pulse1.SpecificTerms | Where-Object { $_ -in $Pulse2.SpecificTerms }\r\n    $termRatio = $sharedTerms.Count / [Math]::Max(1, ($Pulse1.SpecificTerms.Count + $Pulse2.SpecificTerms.Count) / 2)\r\n    if ($termRatio -gt 0.3) { $sharedFeatures++ }\r\n    \r\n    $similarity = $sharedFeatures / $totalFeatures\r\n    return @{\r\n        IsInvariant = $similarity -gt 0.6\r\n        Similarity = $similarity\r\n        SharedTerms = $sharedTerms\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Test-NextPulsePrediction {\r\n    param($TrainingSet, $TestPulse)\r\n    \r\n    # Predict: if content appeared in most recent pulses, it will appear next\r\n    $predictedContent = @{}\r\n    \r\n    foreach ($pulse in $TrainingSet) {\r\n        foreach ($term in $pulse.SpecificTerms) {\r\n            if (-not $predictedContent.ContainsKey($term)) {\r\n                $predictedContent[$term] =\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 18:11:00\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774304461958}}
