{"type":"message","id":"c2ceaa1d","parentId":"fc1ace03","timestamp":"2026-03-23T22:21:41.464Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So there's a new mutation file created: `2026-03-23 182034.mutation`. And there's already a TIC_EXPERIMENT.md and TIC_RESULTS.md in the research directory. Let me read the mutation file and the TIC_RESULTS to understand the current state.","thinkingSignature":"0930208510dc73be5d4f27451cff01d41f464cca1c233e2d03b31a6d5a958e00"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5izlknps2a7r_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\mutations\\proposed\\2026-03-23 182034.mutation"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5izlknps2a7r_2","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\research\\TIC_RESULTS.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":6191,"output":149,"cacheRead":11887,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18227,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774304497939}}
{"type":"message","id":"b8aa2f55","parentId":"c2ceaa1d","timestamp":"2026-03-23T22:21:41.478Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_5izlknps2a7r_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"the\n---\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\n# Phase 1 Advancement: Testing COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\n\nparam(\n    [string]$LogDir = \"logs\",\n    [int]$Lookback = 5,\n    [float]$MinInvarianceScore = 0.6\n)\n\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\n\n# --- Core TIC Functions ---\n\nfunction Get-PulseContent {\n    param([string]$Path)\n    $content = Get-Content $Path -Raw -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\n    if (-not $content) { return $null }\n    return @{\n        Path = $Path\n        Name = [System.IO.Path]::GetFileNameWithoutExtension($Path)\n        RawContent = $content\n        Lines = ($content -split \"`n\").Trim() | Where-Object { $_ }\n    }\n}\n\nfunction Get-PulseHistory {\n    param([string]$LogDir, [int]$Count)\n    if (-not (Test-Path $LogDir)) {\n        Write-Warning \"Log directory not found: $LogDir\"\n        return @()\n    }\n    Get-ChildItem \"$LogDir/pulse_*.md\" | \n        Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending |\n        Select-Object -First $Count |\n        ForEach-Object { Get-PulseContent $_.FullName }\n}\n\nfunction Get-NGrams {\n    param([string[]]$Tokens, [int]$N = 2)\n    $ngrams = @()\n    for ($i = 0; $i -le $tokens.Length - $N; $i++) {\n        $ngram = ($tokens[$i..($i + $N - 1)] -join \" \").ToLower()\n        $ngrams += $ngram\n    }\n    return $ngrams\n}\n\nfunction Measure-InvarianceScore {\n    param([array]$CurrentNGrams, [array]$PriorNGrams)\n    if ($PriorNGrams.Count -eq 0) { return 0.5 }  # Unknown = neutral\n    $overlap = ($CurrentNGrams | Where-Object { $_ -in $PriorNGrams }).Count\n    if ($CurrentNGrams.Count -eq 0) { return 0.5 }\n    return $overlap / $CurrentNGrams.Count\n}\n\nfunction ClassifyPulse {\n    param($Pulse, [array]$PriorNGrams, [float]$Threshold = 0.6)\n    $tokens = $Pulse.Lines | ForEach-Object { ($_ -split \"\\s+\").Trim() } | Where-Object { $_ }\n    $ngrams = Get-NGrams -Tokens $tokens -N 2\n    $score = Measure-InvarianceScore -CurrentNGrams $ngrams -PriorNGrams $PriorNGrams\n    return @{\n        Pulse = $Pulse.Name\n        Score = $score\n        Classification = if ($score -ge $Threshold) { \"INVARIANT\" } else { \"VARIANT\" }\n        NGramCount = $ngrams.Count\n    }\n}\n\nfunction PredictNextPulse {\n    param([array]$InvariantPulses, [int]$TopN = 5)\n    # Build topic model from invariant pulses\n    $allNGrams = @()\n    foreach ($pulse in $InvariantPulses) {\n        $tokens = $pulse.Lines | ForEach-Object { ($_ -split \"\\s+\").Trim() } | Where-Object { $_ }\n        $allNGrams += Get-NGrams -Tokens $tokens -N 2\n    }\n    $freq = $allNGrams | Group-Object | Sort-Object Count -Descending\n    return ($freq | Select-Object -First $TopN).Name\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774304501475}}
{"type":"message","id":"adfad866","parentId":"b8aa2f55","timestamp":"2026-03-23T22:21:41.483Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_5izlknps2a7r_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# TIC Experiment Results — 2026-03-23 10:05\n\n## Setup\n- Pulse logs analyzed: 25\n- Time range: 03/22/2026 01:28:32 → 03/23/2026 07:04:18\n- Invariant threshold: streak >= 3 consecutive pulses\n- Variant threshold: streak <= 1\n\n## Invariant Classification\n- Invariant elements (streak >= 3): 8\n- Variant elements (streak <= 1): 0\n- Key invariants: pulse, Phase 1, Sandbox, Breakaway, Phase 0, GAP, llm, TemporalAttention\n\n## Prediction Test\n- Pairs evaluated: 21\n- Mean Precision: 90%\n- Mean Recall: 88.5%\n- Random baseline: ~5%\n- Result: BETTER THAN RANDOM\n\n## Gap Sensitivity\n- Small gaps (<30 min) Jaccard: 0.704\n- Medium gaps (30-120m) Jaccard: 1\n- Large gaps (>120 min) Jaccard: 0.834\n- Hypothesis (shorter gap → more overlap): REJECTED\n\n## Phase Persistence\n  Phase 0 COMPLETE: streak=17   Phase 1 COMPLETE: streak=17\n\n## TIC Score: 2/3\n## VERDICT: SUPPORTED\n\n## Implications\n- If SUPPORTED: compression=causal hypothesis is empirically grounded for Breakaway pulses\n- Invariant elements = causal anchors (Phase status, research topic persistence)\n- Gap size can be used to weight reconstruction confidence\n- Next: Use invariants as fixed points in compression, treat variants as contingent details\n\n## Next Experiment\n- Train actual embedding-based compressor on Paperspace GPU\n- Measure: does cosine similarity between pulse embeddings correlate with Jaccard?\n- Success criteria: >60% next-pulse prediction using only embedding dot products\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774304501480}}
