{"type":"message","id":"8668e349","parentId":"4431431b","timestamp":"2026-03-23T22:21:59.243Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_47xk4x4p83pe_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"commit 6fd5392df2178a7f2f8c834e92423a4012a040b2\nAuthor: Sandbox <sandbox@breakaway>\nDate:   Mon Mar 23 18:21:01 2026 -0400\n\n    pulse: 2026-03-23 182034\n\n .llm_prompt.txt                                    |   2 +-\n .llm_response.txt                                  | 175 ++++++++++-----------\n .mutation_parse_result.json                        |   2 +-\n memory/session/pulse_2026-03-23 182034.md          | 129 +++++++++++++++\n mutations/proposed/2026-03-23 182034.mutation      |  83 ++++++++++\n .../2026-03-23 181034.mutation                     |   0\n state/autonomous_pulse.md                          |   2 +\n 7 files changed, 301 insertions(+), 92 deletions(-)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1168,"aggregated":"commit 6fd5392df2178a7f2f8c834e92423a4012a040b2\nAuthor: Sandbox <sandbox@breakaway>\nDate:   Mon Mar 23 18:21:01 2026 -0400\n\n    pulse: 2026-03-23 182034\n\n .llm_prompt.txt                                    |   2 +-\n .llm_response.txt                                  | 175 ++++++++++-----------\n .mutation_parse_result.json                        |   2 +-\n memory/session/pulse_2026-03-23 182034.md          | 129 +++++++++++++++\n mutations/proposed/2026-03-23 182034.mutation      |  83 ++++++++++\n .../2026-03-23 181034.mutation                     |   0\n state/autonomous_pulse.md                          |   2 +\n 7 files changed, 301 insertions(+), 92 deletions(-)","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774304519240}}
{"type":"message","id":"6928d535","parentId":"8668e349","timestamp":"2026-03-23T22:22:06.188Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the commit shows:\n1. The mutation was successfully parsed - the mutation proposed file was created\n2. The pulse log was created \n3. The previous mutation was renamed to rejected\n4. But the `src/TIC-Classifier.ps1` file was NOT created in this commit\n\nThe mutation parse result shows the issue - the old_text was '(new file)' and the file inferred was empty. This is why the new file wasn't created.\n\nThe current state:\n- TIC-Classifier.ps1 was NOT actually created (src directory doesn't exist)\n- A new mutation is proposed that SHOULD create src/TIC-Classifier.ps1 if applied\n- The TIC experiment already has results documented in TIC_RESULTS.md\n\n\n- The 181034 mutation got rejected due to a truncation bug, and now there's a new mutation trying to create the TIC-Classifier.ps1 file\n\nI should check what the most recent memory/session/pulse_2026-03-23 182034.md file actually contains.","thinkingSignature":"402197b7181aafb1b8a1f3da030a7f6354822284af4e00f11f3109fd7d3a0814"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9smyfqrcbhu3_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-23 182034.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":8147,"output":257,"cacheRead":11887,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":20291,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774304519245}}
{"type":"message","id":"1e9685b9","parentId":"6928d535","timestamp":"2026-03-23T22:22:06.198Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_9smyfqrcbhu3_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-23 182034\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: src/TIC-Experiment.ps1 (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me review the current state and determine what single concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nFrom the context:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 architecture analysis are complete\r\n- There's a key insight about COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\r\n- The next action is the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Experiment\r\n- Need to implement TIC classifier on pulse logs\r\n- Recent pulse: pulse_2026-03-23 181034.md\r\n\r\nLooking at the pending actions:\r\n1. Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n2. Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\r\n3. Tune λ empirically (start: λ=0.7)\r\n4. Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n5. Measure compression ratio: original vs. summarized pulse\r\n\r\nThe NEXT ACTION from Phase 1 Advancement is the TIC Experiment:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nI should take a concrete step toward implementing the TIC experiment. Let me look at the existing pulse logs to understand their structure, then create a basic TIC implementation.\r\n\r\nLet me first check what files exist in the sandbox, particularly in logs/ and research/ directories.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\nLooking at the current state, the most impactful single action is to begin the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment. I'll create the initial TIC classifier implementation to analyze pulse logs for invariant/variant patterns.\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment is the next critical step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis, but there's no implementation yet. I need to build the classifier to analyze existing pulse logs.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the initial TIC classifier script that will analyze pulse logs for invariant/variant patterns and attempt to predict subsequent pulse content.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n# Phase 1 Advancement: Testing COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis\r\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [string]$LogDir = \"logs\",\r\n    [int]$Lookback = 5,\r\n    [float]$MinInvarianceScore = 0.6\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\n# --- Core TIC Functions ---\r\n\r\nfunction Get-PulseContent {\r\n    param([string]$Path)\r\n    $content = Get-Content $Path -Raw -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\r\n    if (-not $content) { return $null }\r\n    return @{\r\n        Path = $Path\r\n        Name = [System.IO.Path]::GetFileNameWithoutExtension($Path)\r\n        RawContent = $content\r\n        Lines = ($content -split \"`n\").Trim() | Where-Object { $_ }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Get-PulseHistory {\r\n    param([string]$LogDir, [int]$Count)\r\n    if (-not (Test-Path $LogDir)) {\r\n        Write-Warning \"Log directory not found: $LogDir\"\r\n        return @()\r\n    }\r\n    Get-ChildItem \"$LogDir/pulse_*.md\" | \r\n        Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending |\r\n        Select-Object -First $Count |\r\n        ForEach-Object { Get-PulseContent $_.FullName }\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Get-NGrams {\r\n    param([string[]]$Tokens, [int]$N = 2)\r\n    $ngrams = @()\r\n    for ($i = 0; $i -le $tokens.Length - $N; $i++) {\r\n        $ngram = ($tokens[$i..($i + $N - 1)] -join \" \").ToLower()\r\n        $ngrams += $ngram\r\n    }\r\n    return $ngrams\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Measure-InvarianceScore {\r\n    param([array]$CurrentNGrams, [array]$PriorNGrams)\r\n    if ($PriorNGrams.Count -eq 0) { return 0.5 }  # Unknown = neutral\r\n    $overlap = ($CurrentNGrams | Where-Object { $_ -in $PriorNGrams }).Count\r\n    if ($CurrentNGrams.Count -eq 0) { return 0.5 }\r\n    return $overlap / $CurrentNGrams.Count\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction ClassifyPulse {\r\n    param($Pulse, [array]$PriorNGrams, [float]$Threshold = 0.6)\r\n    $tokens = $Pulse.Lines | ForEach-Object { ($_ -split \"\\s+\").Trim() } | Where-Object { $_ }\r\n    $ngrams = Get-NGrams -Tokens $tokens -N 2\r\n    $score = Measure-InvarianceScore -CurrentNGrams $ngrams -PriorNGrams $PriorNGrams\r\n    return @{\r\n        Pulse = $Pulse.Name\r\n        Score = $score\r\n        Classification = if ($score -ge $Threshold) { \"INVARIANT\" } else { \"VARIANT\" }\r\n        NGramCount = $ngrams.Count\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction PredictNextPulse {\r\n    param([array]$InvariantPulses, [int]$TopN = 5)\r\n    # Build topic model from invariant pulses\r\n    $allNGrams = @()\r\n    foreach ($pulse in $InvariantPulses) {\r\n        $tokens = $pulse.Lines | ForEach-Object { ($_ -split \"\\s+\").Trim() } | Where-Object { $_ }\r\n        $allNGrams += Get-NGrams -Tokens $tokens -N 2\r\n    }\r\n    $freq = $allNGrams | Group-Object | Sort-Object Count -Descending\r\n    return ($freq | Select-Object -First $TopN).Name\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 18:21:01\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774304526195}}
{"type":"message","id":"68e2337f","parentId":"1e9685b9","timestamp":"2026-03-23T22:22:11.738Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, the log file content is the same as the previous one. But the exec output showed that a NEW mutation was created (2026-03-23 182034.mutation) which was different from the previous one (which had a bug with the cut-off code). Let me re-read this more carefully.\n\nWait - looking at the git show output:\n```\nmutations/proposed/2026-03-23 182034.mutation      |  83 ++++++++++\n```\n\nThis is 83 lines. And the file I read shows 202 lines. So either the file has grown, or I'm reading an older version.\n\nLet me re-read the actual newest mutation file.","thinkingSignature":"80605c5b3738ad36ab5d475cf04cfa3015bab25a3453d72cc2cc41cae8bda8ea"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_susaca8wow8u_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-Content \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\mutations\\proposed\\2026-03-23 182034.mutation\" -Raw"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":9666,"output":200,"cacheRead":11887,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21753,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774304526199}}
{"type":"message","id":"861716c7","parentId":"68e2337f","timestamp":"2026-03-23T22:22:12.773Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_susaca8wow8u_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"the\n---\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\n# Phase 1 Advancement: Testing COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\n\nparam(\n    [string]$LogDir = \"logs\",\n    [int]$Lookback = 5,\n    [float]$MinInvarianceScore = 0.6\n)\n\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\n\n# --- Core TIC Functions ---\n\nfunction Get-PulseContent {\n    param([string]$Path)\n    $content = Get-Content $Path -Raw -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\n    if (-not $content) { return $null }\n    return @{\n        Path = $Path\n        Name = [System.IO.Path]::GetFileNameWithoutExtension($Path)\n        RawContent = $content\n        Lines = ($content -split \"`n\").Trim() | Where-Object { $_ }\n    }\n}\n\nfunction Get-PulseHistory {\n    param([string]$LogDir, [int]$Count)\n    if (-not (Test-Path $LogDir)) {\n        Write-Warning \"Log directory not found: $LogDir\"\n        return @()\n    }\n    Get-ChildItem \"$LogDir/pulse_*.md\" | \n        Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending |\n        Select-Object -First $Count |\n        ForEach-Object { Get-PulseContent $_.FullName }\n}\n\nfunction Get-NGrams {\n    param([string[]]$Tokens, [int]$N = 2)\n    $ngrams = @()\n    for ($i = 0; $i -le $tokens.Length - $N; $i++) {\n        $ngram = ($tokens[$i..($i + $N - 1)] -join \" \").ToLower()\n        $ngrams += $ngram\n    }\n    return $ngrams\n}\n\nfunction Measure-InvarianceScore {\n    param([array]$CurrentNGrams, [array]$PriorNGrams)\n    if ($PriorNGrams.Count -eq 0) { return 0.5 }  # Unknown = neutral\n    $overlap = ($CurrentNGrams | Where-Object { $_ -in $PriorNGrams }).Count\n    if ($CurrentNGrams.Count -eq 0) { return 0.5 }\n    return $overlap / $CurrentNGrams.Count\n}\n\nfunction ClassifyPulse {\n    param($Pulse, [array]$PriorNGrams, [float]$Threshold = 0.6)\n    $tokens = $Pulse.Lines | ForEach-Object { ($_ -split \"\\s+\").Trim() } | Where-Object { $_ }\n    $ngrams = Get-NGrams -Tokens $tokens -N 2\n    $score = Measure-InvarianceScore -CurrentNGrams $ngrams -PriorNGrams $PriorNGrams\n    return @{\n        Pulse = $Pulse.Name\n        Score = $score\n        Classification = if ($score -ge $Threshold) { \"INVARIANT\" } else { \"VARIANT\" }\n        NGramCount = $ngrams.Count\n    }\n}\n\nfunction PredictNextPulse {\n    param([array]$InvariantPulses, [int]$TopN = 5)\n    # Build topic model from invariant pulses\n    $allNGrams = @()\n    foreach ($pulse in $InvariantPulses) {\n        $tokens = $pulse.Lines | ForEach-Object { ($_ -split \"\\s+\").Trim() } | Where-Object { $_ }\n        $allNGrams += Get-NGrams -Tokens $tokens -N 2\n    }\n    $freq = $allNGrams | Group-Object | Sort-Object Count -Descending\n    return ($freq | Select-Object -First $TopN).Name"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1029,"aggregated":"the\n---\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\n# Phase 1 Advancement: Testing COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\n\nparam(\n    [string]$LogDir = \"logs\",\n    [int]$Lookback = 5,\n    [float]$MinInvarianceScore = 0.6\n)\n\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\n\n# --- Core TIC Functions ---\n\nfunction Get-PulseContent {\n    param([string]$Path)\n    $content = Get-Content $Path -Raw -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\n    if (-not $content) { return $null }\n    return @{\n        Path = $Path\n        Name = [System.IO.Path]::GetFileNameWithoutExtension($Path)\n        RawContent = $content\n        Lines = ($content -split \"`n\").Trim() | Where-Object { $_ }\n    }\n}\n\nfunction Get-PulseHistory {\n    param([string]$LogDir, [int]$Count)\n    if (-not (Test-Path $LogDir)) {\n        Write-Warning \"Log directory not found: $LogDir\"\n        return @()\n    }\n    Get-ChildItem \"$LogDir/pulse_*.md\" | \n        Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending |\n        Select-Object -First $Count |\n        ForEach-Object { Get-PulseContent $_.FullName }\n}\n\nfunction Get-NGrams {\n    param([string[]]$Tokens, [int]$N = 2)\n    $ngrams = @()\n    for ($i = 0; $i -le $tokens.Length - $N; $i++) {\n        $ngram = ($tokens[$i..($i + $N - 1)] -join \" \").ToLower()\n        $ngrams += $ngram\n    }\n    return $ngrams\n}\n\nfunction Measure-InvarianceScore {\n    param([array]$CurrentNGrams, [array]$PriorNGrams)\n    if ($PriorNGrams.Count -eq 0) { return 0.5 }  # Unknown = neutral\n    $overlap = ($CurrentNGrams | Where-Object { $_ -in $PriorNGrams }).Count\n    if ($CurrentNGrams.Count -eq 0) { return 0.5 }\n    return $overlap / $CurrentNGrams.Count\n}\n\nfunction ClassifyPulse {\n    param($Pulse, [array]$PriorNGrams, [float]$Threshold = 0.6)\n    $tokens = $Pulse.Lines | ForEach-Object { ($_ -split \"\\s+\").Trim() } | Where-Object { $_ }\n    $ngrams = Get-NGrams -Tokens $tokens -N 2\n    $score = Measure-InvarianceScore -CurrentNGrams $ngrams -PriorNGrams $PriorNGrams\n    return @{\n        Pulse = $Pulse.Name\n        Score = $score\n        Classification = if ($score -ge $Threshold) { \"INVARIANT\" } else { \"VARIANT\" }\n        NGramCount = $ngrams.Count\n    }\n}\n\nfunction PredictNextPulse {\n    param([array]$InvariantPulses, [int]$TopN = 5)\n    # Build topic model from invariant pulses\n    $allNGrams = @()\n    foreach ($pulse in $InvariantPulses) {\n        $tokens = $pulse.Lines | ForEach-Object { ($_ -split \"\\s+\").Trim() } | Where-Object { $_ }\n        $allNGrams += Get-NGrams -Tokens $tokens -N 2\n    }\n    $freq = $allNGrams | Group-Object | Sort-Object Count -Descending\n    return ($freq | Select-Object -First $TopN).Name","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timest